The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, Aug. 7: Calcutta High Court sentenced two persons to 10 years rigorous imprisonment for raping a girl at Contai in East Midnapore in 1985. Mantu Raut and Uday Jana were convicted by a Midnapore court in 1988 and sentenced to jail for 10 years. But, the same year, the high court had granted them interim bail. Both Raut and Jana had moved an appeal before the high court challenging the verdict of the trial court. On Monday, a division bench of the court upheld the earlier verdict.

 Midnapore: A visually challenged woman and her 15-year-old daughter were electrocuted on Monday morning after they came in contact with a live wire lying on a field at Gopalnagar in Kolaghat area of East Midnapore. Kanchan Kapat, 36, was walking in a field with her daughter, Tumpa. She asked her daughter to wait on one side of the field and went to relieve herself when she stepped on the live wire. Tumpa rushed to help her but the girl, too, was electrocuted.

 Krishnagar: A 30-year-old man was arrested on Sunday night on the charge of theft of about 250 gm of gold and Rs 2,000 from a jewellery shop in Haryana where he used to work. A joint police team of Nadia and Haryana arrested Kishan Basak in Nadia. 

 Calcutta: Transport minister Subhas Chakraborty will meet civil aviation minister Praful Patel in Delhi on August 9 and submit a proposal seeking conversion of abandoned air strips in eight Bengal districts into small airports.




